Package com.google.api.client.json

Class CustomizeJsonParser

Customizes the behavior of a JSON parser.

All methods have a default trivial implementation, so subclasses need only only implement the methodsmethods whose behavior needs customization. @since 1.0 @author Yaniv Inbar

Class GenericJson

Generic JSON data that stores all unknown key name/value pairs.

Subclasses can declare fields for known data keys using the Key annotation. Each fieldfield can be of any visibility (private, package private, protected, or public) and must not be static. {@code null} unknown data key key names are not allowed, but {@code null} data values are allowed. @since 1.0 @author Yaniv Inbar

Class JsonHttpContent

Serializes JSON HTTP content based on the data key/value mapping object for for an item.

Sample usage: 

 
 static void setContent(HttpRequest request, Object data) {
   JsonHttpContent content = new JsonHttpContent();
   content.data = data;
   request.content = content;
 }
@since 1.0 @author Yaniv Inbar
Class JsonHttpParser

Parses HTTP JSON response content into an data class of key/value pairs.

Sample usage: 

 
 static void setParser(HttpTransport transport) {
   transport.addParser(new JsonHttpParser());
 }
@since 1.0 @author Yaniv Inbar
Class JsonHttpParser, JsonParser parserForResponse(HttpResponse)

Returns a JSON parser to use for parsing the given HTTP response.

The response content will be closed if any throwable is thrown. On success, the current tokentoken will be the first key in the JSON object. @param response HTTP response @return JSON parser @throws IllegalArgumentException if content type is not not Json.CONTENT_TYPE @throws IOException I/O exception
